# GeoMoney Web App Overhaul

The site currently has a single-page layout where Hero, News, Videos, Rare Earth, Tools, and Newsletter are all stacked on one page. The AI Navigation assistant navigates to hash anchors (e.g., `/#news-grid`) which provides minimal value. News has no geopolitics filters. The article detail page has a poor sticky sidebar. Videos have no type differentiation. Several feature pages show "Coming Soon" and Tools page has locked "PRO" features.

This overhaul re-architects the site into distinct routed pages, adds filtering/configuration, unlocks all features, and polishes the UI/UX.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Multi-page routing split**: The homepage will be simplified to Hero + Feature Cards + a brief news preview (3 articles) + Newsletter CTA. Full content moves to dedicated pages (`/news`, `/videos`, `/tools`, `/materials`). The AI Navigator will route users to these real pages instead of hash anchors.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Prisma schema change**: Adding a `videoType` field to the `Video` model. This requires running `npx prisma db push` or a migration. Make sure the database is accessible.

> [!WARNING]
> **Pro features unlock**: All locked Pro features in Tools page will be unlocked and made fully functional (no paywall). The "Subscribe to Unlock" buttons will be removed.

